# React & UI components

**Authoritative source:** [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) §1 (stack), §5 (conventions), and the **nearest `AGENTS.md`** for the app under `apps/*`. **`AGENTS.md` wins** on any conflict.

## Stack pointers

- **Framework:** Next.js **App Router** (not Pages Router for new work) → versions per **`AGENTS.md` §1** (Next.js 15–16).
- **UI:** **React 19**; styling **Tailwind CSS v4** (**`AGENTS.md` §1**).
- **Shared UI & tokens:** prefer **`packages/sentra-ui`** and **`packages/design-token`** when building product UI instead of one-off styles → match existing app patterns first.

## Sentra / healthcare UI

- For **Sentra** visual governance (Clinical Aura, Living Edge, design tokens), use the **Sentra design skill** / design protocol when the task is product UI → stay consistent with existing screens in the target app.
- **PHI:** never embed real patient data in components, Storybook, fixtures, or screenshots; use placeholders (**`AGENTS.md` §5**).

## Structure

- Follow the **folder and naming conventions** of the app being edited (`apps/<division>/<app>/`).
- **Accessibility:** preserve semantic HTML, labels, and keyboard flows consistent with adjacent components.

## Hierarchy

- Root **`AGENTS.md`** → division **`apps/*/AGENTS.md`** → package **`AGENTS.md`** (if present). Apply the **strictest** rule that applies to the task.

## Gold standard references

- Follow component patterns in `@packages/sentra-ui/src/components/ui/`.
- Follow design token usage in `@packages/design-token/src/`.

## Design token enforcement (agent behavior)

- For any UI change, agents must use existing design tokens first.
- Do not add inline color literals (`#`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`, `hsl()`) in
  component files unless the app `AGENTS.md` explicitly allows the exception.
- Prefer CSS variables from the target app token system (example: `--fi-*`) for
  color, spacing, radius, shadow, and motion where available.
- If a new token is required, agents must:
  1) declare it in the app token source,
  2) replace usage sites to reference the token,
  3) update token docs (`docs/token/*`) in the same task.

